<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="O" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Oil" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Oil,</orth> unctuous substance used for various purposes, chiefly for nourishing the flame in lamps: <bibl n="shak. ven 756" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 756</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.153" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 153</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 1, 65</bibl> (== train-oil). <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.39" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.1.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 1, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.2.59" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 2, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.7" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 3.2.178" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 2, 178</bibl> <emph>(boiling in leads or --s;</emph> Walker <cit><quote>in lead or o.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.7" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 7</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.8" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.2.55" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 2, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.1.88" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 1, 88</bibl> <cit><quote>(holy oil).</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 1, 61</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.2.140" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 2, 140</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.2.83" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 2, 83</bibl>.
